You can use the like function to check it a string matches a certain pattern.
 The like function returns true if the pattern matches and falseif it doent match.

See the following example:

|eval errorType = if (like (error, "javasException"), "Java Exception", "Unknown Error")

 You can use case function if you have multiple values to match. For example:
 index= main sourcetype=access_combined_wcookie
|eval httpStatusCategory= case (status== 200, "OK", status >=400 AND status < 500, "client Error", status 500,
 "Server Error", 1=1 "N/A")

|stats count by httpStatusCategory

